── PROFILE PAGE (showshak-profile.html) ────────────────────────

  THREE FACES, ONE PAGE (philosophy: "show identity & taste,
  hide the scoreboard"). A prototype "Preview as" switcher in the
  hero stands in for real auth and lets you demo all three:
    - face='user'   → a normal user viewing THEIR OWN profile
    - face='owner'  → a curator viewing THEIR OWN profile (cockpit)
    - face='public' → ANYONE viewing a curator (trust surface)
  Legacy `isCreator` is kept, DERIVED from face (= owner||public),
  so the existing .is-creator CSS keeps working. setFace(f) re-renders
  everything via renderAll(). toggleMode() is a back-compat alias.

  THE METRICS RULE (deliberate, do not "simplify" away):
    - NEVER show a user their "fires given" — fire is a free reflex;
      counting it back makes users ration it. Removed from the page.
    - User has NO "liked/fired clips" archive for the same reason.
      Instead the user gets HISTORY (recently watched), a neutral
      WATCH log (not a like log) that solves "I lost a clip and the
      algorithm won't resurface it" — 7-day, clearable.
    - PUBLIC curator profile shows ONLY Followers + Clips (standing +
      substance). NEVER fires-received or Watch-It taps (those are the
      reflex + the money → popularity contest). Those live ONLY in the
      owner's private cockpit.
    - OWNER curator: Followers + Following + Clips in the bar, PLUS a
      private cockpit (Fires · Watch-Its · Reach) shown ABOVE the clips
      (#cockpit) so it's the first thing the curator sees, marked
      "Only you can see this".

  Header (cinematic hero, no plain cover — built from the curator's
  own clip gradients, blurred):
    - avatar (#av), letter or uploaded photo; 🔥 flame badge via .is-creator
    - name, @handle, "Curating since 2023"
    - bio + taste tags (PROFILE.genres)
    - NO social media links — by design. We keep people ON ShowShak,
      not bouncing out to Instagram/X. (Removed 2026.)
    - hero actions per face:
        user   → Edit Profile ONLY (a user profile is private — no one
                 else sees it, so there is nothing to Share). The hero-top
                 Share icon is also hidden on the user face.
        owner  → Edit Profile + Share + "View as public"
        public → Follow + Share  (togglePublicFollow)

  Credentials bar (#creds): face-aware via renderCreds() per rule above.

  Highlights shelf (#shelf): fanned "stack spine" cards (NOT IG circles).
    - public face → ONLY public collections, no share/new buttons, empty
      state if none. owner/user → all, with visibility chips + share + new.

  Tabs (renderTabs, face-aware; panels: create/primary/stacks/history/
  analytics/following):
    - user   → History | Following
    - public → Clips | Shared Stacks
    - owner  → Create | My Clips | Collections | Analytics | Following

  Modals (unchanged, still excellent):
    - Become a Curator (#bc-overlay): 3-step flow; on activate →
      face='owner', lands on Create tab.
    - Edit Profile (#ep-overlay): identity only (photo, name, bio,
      + specialties for curators). Stays IN the profile page.

  Settings: the ⚙ (hero top-right AND sidebar) now navigates to the
  separate showshak-settings.html (NOT a modal). goSettings().

  All data is MOCK (hardcoded) — no real auth yet.

  Key functions:
    setFace(f) / renderAll()  switch face + full re-render
    renderHeader()            identity + socials + actions + cockpit + creds
    renderCockpit()           owner-only private metrics, above clips
    renderCreds()             face-aware stats bar (the metrics rule)
    renderTabs()/switchTab()  face-aware tabs + panel switching
    renderPrimary()           curator clips grid (owner + public)
    renderHistory()           user 7-day recently-watched (clearHistory)
    renderShelf()             highlights; public-only filter on public face
