── SETTINGS PAGE (showshak-settings.html) ──────────────────────

  Separate page (NOT a modal) — uses the shared CSS/JS contract.
  Single page with drill-in sub-screens (acts like a page within a
  page): a nav `stack[]` + go()/settingsBack(); browser/hardware back
  pops a sub-screen before leaving to the profile.

  Two scopes (the creator block appears only when SET_IS_CREATOR;
  toggled by a prototype switch on the home screen, persisted in
  sessionStorage 'ss_is_creator_v1' — fresh-start by design like the
  rest of the app; body.is-creator gates .creator-only):

    SHARED (everyone):
      Account (email, password, logins, deactivate/delete)
      My Platforms — subscription data lives HERE, framed as Watch It
        routing ("so we send you to the right place"), never a profile
        badge. (Resolves the no-vanity-subscriptions decision.)
      Region & Language — region drives Watch It availability
      Notifications — DIGEST by default; fires are a weekly summary,
        NEVER a per-fire ping (avoids the influencer-metrics treadmill)
      Privacy — shared-stack visibility, clear history, personalization
      Playback — autoplay, start muted, data saver
      Support & About — help, feedback, report, Terms, Privacy, DMCA

    CREATOR ONLY:
      Creator Profile (public bio, handle, verification)
      Creator Tools (upload defaults, manage clips, drafts)
      Payouts & Monetization (payout account, earnings, promoted clips)
      Analytics (quick this-week numbers → link to full dashboard)

  Distinction from Edit Profile: Edit Profile = identity shown ON the
  profile (photo/name/bio/taste), stays in profile.html. Settings =
  account, app behavior, money, legal — everything else.



