── WHAT MAKES SHOWSHAK DIFFERENT ───────────────────────────────

  NOT Instagram/TikTok: clips are not the destination, they are
  a window. The show IS the destination. Curators are not
  influencers — they are taste authorities.

  NOT Netflix: we don't own the content. We send users TO the
  platform. We are the bridge, not the destination.

  THE GAP WE FILL: human taste + cross-platform + action.
  "Your most trusted film-obsessed friend, with a platform."


── CONTENT MODEL — CLIP, CAPTION, TAGS & UPLOAD ────────────────

  THE CORE PRINCIPLE:
  The curator makes their OWN content to promote a show. Keep their
  job minimal. They provide a few things; the SYSTEM derives the rest.

  WHAT THE CURATOR PROVIDES (the entire upload):
    1. Their clip            (the video — their content)        REQUIRED
    2. Their caption / pitch (a real paragraph, see below)      REQUIRED
    3. The show/movie        (ONE tap — pick from a list)       REQUIRED
    4. A vibe / "why watch"  (1–3 from a fixed set)             OPTIONAL

  WHAT THE SYSTEM DERIVES AUTOMATICALLY (curator never types this):
    - Genre, year, cast, language        ← from the picked show (TMDB)
    - Platform + Watch It deep-link      ← resolved from show + region
    - Platform color / label on the rail ← from resolved platform
    - Algorithm signals                  ← mined from the caption text

  ── CAPTION (the pitch) ─────────────────────────────────────
    REQUIRED. NOT a one-liner. Target ~70–90 words so the curator
    can properly express and tell a bigger story — tone, emotion,
    what they're promising, why it hit them. This is the heart of
    the trust-based model (CREATOR FIRST, SHOW SECOND) and our
    single richest future algorithm signal (sentiment, theme,
    intensity, mood). Enforce a minimum length so it stays a real
    pitch, not "🔥🔥". The title is NEVER revealed in the caption.

    Display: feed/grid shows a clamped preview ("…more"); the FULL
    caption is readable in the expanded clip viewer (scrollable).
    The line-clamp on .caption / .ssv-caption is preview-only and
    will get a "more" expansion when real data is wired.

  ── TAGS — DECISION: NO open hashtags ───────────────────────
    We deliberately do NOT use Instagram-style free hashtags in the
    caption. They invite spam (#fyp #viral) that pollutes search and
    POISONS the algorithm with noise. Instead we use STRUCTURED
    signals that stay clean and finite:

      a) SHOW PICK   → gives us genre/language/platform for free
      b) VIBE PICKER → 1–3 from the fixed mood set already used on
                       Discover (Edge of My Seat, Feel Good, Want to
                       Cry, Date Night, Mind-Bending, Family Night,
                       Late Night, Laugh Out Loud). Controlled list,
                       zero spam, perfect algorithm fuel.
      c) CAPTION MINING → we extract themes/emotion from the caption
                       text on OUR side. The curator writes naturally;
                       we derive the tags. No tag field to spam.

    Any user-facing "tag" discovery surface is built from OUR derived
    tags + vibe picks (our taxonomy) — never from curator free text.

  ── DATA MODEL (3 linked entities — build it this way) ──────
    CREATOR  (handle, avatar, verified, general bio) → has many clips
    CLIP     (video, caption/pitch, fire & save counts, vibe[])
               → belongs to a Creator, points to a Title
    TITLE    (name, year, poster, synopsis, platforms/availability)
               → pulled from TMDB; ONE record shared by all clips
                 about that show (unlocks "all clips for this show",
                 reliable Watch It links, clean analytics)

    The action rail (Fire, Save, Share, Watch It) is a CONSTANT frame
    on every clip — only the DATA inside it swaps per clip.


── LEGAL & CONTENT STRATEGY (READ BEFORE SCALING) ──────────────

  This is a deliberate strategic stance, not legal advice. Get a
  real entertainment/IP lawyer before public launch or fundraising.

  THE RISK:
  ShowShak's value depends on short clips of copyrighted shows and
  movies. "It's fair use, like YouTube/TikTok do it" is NOT a safe
  assumption. Fair use is a case-by-case US legal defense (4-factor
  test), not a blanket shield — and it is NOT what actually protects
  the big platforms.

  WHAT ACTUALLY PROTECTS COMPARABLE PLATFORMS:
    - DMCA safe harbor: they are HOSTS. Users upload; the platform
      removes infringing content on valid notice and bans repeat
      infringers. The platform itself does not upload.
    - Content ID + direct licensing: YouTube pays/monetizes rights
      holders through automated matching and studio deals.
  Many clip-uploaders are technically infringing; they are tolerated
  or monetized through those systems — not "protected by fair use."

  SHOWSHAK'S STANCE (build this in from the start, it is cheap now):
    1. Position clearly as a HOST/platform for curator-uploaded
       clips — ShowShak does not upload content itself.
    2. DMCA safe-harbor scaffolding before scale:
         - Register a DMCA agent (US Copyright Office).
         - Visible takedown / notice-and-counter-notice process.
         - Repeat-infringer policy with enforcement.
         - Terms of Service putting upload responsibility on the curator.
    3. Long game = the YouTube path: licensing / revenue-share deals
       or official studio-provided clips and trailers.
    4. Do NOT bet the company on "fair use." It is invisible as a
       risk until a studio's legal team makes it very visible.

  WATCH IT — DATA & DEEP-LINKING (you can start TODAY, no deals needed):
    - Streaming availability ("on Netflix/Prime in your region") is
      available now for free via the TMDB API "watch providers"
      endpoint (TMDB licenses this data from JustWatch).
    - The deep link itself (open the Netflix/Prime app to a title)
      uses public universal-link URLs — no partnership required.
    - Partnerships / affiliate networks are needed for GETTING PAID
      on the click (attribution + revenue share), not for the link.
    - Positioning: ShowShak is the emotional, taste-driven top of the
      funnel (curators). JustWatch is a cold utility search box. We
      win on engagement and trust, not on database completeness.


